<br>
But anyway...  I am over the nerf too.  Any melee class can tank slowed mobs.  Monks are much more valuable than just being uber tanks.<br>
<br>
The one thing I feel you did not address, however, is the inconsistency with damage taken.  Without slow, sometimes I cast a CH heal on a mob with 3 bubs remaining and it lands with 2 bubs remaining.  SAME EXACT MOB, I can start at 3 reds and lands at 1.  Before the damage mitigation nerf, I really feel that damage taken was much more consistent and reliable.  But with 1200 AC and 4k+ HPs, defensive warriors always tanked better than me anyway.  Herein lies the source of the complaint.  Regular level 60s like me lost some tanking *consistency* due to maybe the top 5% (or less) of all monks having insane All/All gear.  To balance the 5% they nerfed the rest of us.<br>
<br>
Did I whine about it?  Yeah, I was a bit frustrated.  I vented.  Do I still tank?  All the time.  Is it really *that bad*??  No.  Does it suck?  Absolutely.  Was it a stupid patch?  Without a doubt.<br>
<br>
Now, the main whine you appear to have with Monks is that the &quot;stupid ones&quot; are paralyzed by their whining.  But is one whine any better than another?  I too fall for whine bait all the time unfortunately.  I used to log into guild chat to complaints about overpowering monk weapons coming from PoP.  Its all too easy to start linking my custom thurgadin quest pieces.  I still wear the legs *for the hitpoints*.  They are what, AC 7?<br>
<br>
Its hard to escape whining in EQ.  What I do know is that someone whined, and monks got nerfed.  Then monks whined and perhaps got some badass weapons.  Now people are whining about the weapons.  Whining is a way a life in this game it seems.  Perhaps the best advice is: if you can't handle the whining, find another game, preferably, one that does not involve lots of other people.<br>
<br>
I know I got serious on a stupid post, but true Monks rarely loose their cool or act sophmoric!  Well, besides the drunken Masters perhaps!  And the nerf did upset me, so I am venting a little in my own way.<br>
